<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">New to the Nordic countries.</emphasis>
The species is widely distributed in arid areas of both the Northern and Southern Hemispheres (
<bibRefCitation author="Egea, JM" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Lichenologica" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B19" refString="Egea, JM, 1989. Los generos Heppia y Peltula (Liquenes) en Europa Occidental y Norte de Africa. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 31: 1 - 122" title="Los generos Heppia y Peltula (Liquenes) en Europa Occidental y Norte de Africa." volume="31" year="1989">Egea 1989</bibRefCitation>
). The nearest locality is found in Northern Italy (Vinschgau in South Tyrol; 
<bibRefCitation author="Buschardt, A" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Lichenologica" pageId="22" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 419" refId="B8" refString="Buschardt, A, 1979. Zur Flechtenflora der inneralpinen Trockentaeler unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung des Vinschgaus. Bibliotheca Lichenologica 10: 1 - 419" title="Zur Flechtenflora der inneralpinen Trockentaeler unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung des Vinschgaus." volume="10" year="1979">Buschardt 1979</bibRefCitation>
), and the species fits in the element of continental lichens with a widely disjunct distribution from the Alps to the upper valleys of southeast Norway. Other species with a similar disjunction include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poelt" authorityYear="1974" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Buellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Buellia elegans" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Buellia elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poelt, 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Teloschistaceae" genus="Gyalolechia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gyalolechia desertorum" order="Teloschistales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="desertorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Gyalolechia desertorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tomin) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Søchting">Sochting</normalizedToken>
et al., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timdal" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Schaer." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Psoraceae" genus="Psora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Psora vallesiaca" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vallesiaca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Psora vallesiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schaerer) Timdal, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Timdal" authorityYear="1991" baseAuthorityName="H. Magn." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Catillariaceae" genus="Toninia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Toninia sculpturata" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sculpturata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Toninia sculpturata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H. Magn.) Timdal, 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="T. taurica" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="taurica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">T. taurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Szatala) Oxner, 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecideaceae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="T. tristis" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">T. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Th. Fr.) Th. Fr., and 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Teloschistaceae" genus="Xanthocarpia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xanthocarpia tominii" order="Teloschistales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tominii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Xanthocarpia tominii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Savicz) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Frödén">Froeden</normalizedToken>
et al. The species is recognized by the crustose to subsquamulose, dark olivaceous brown thallus composed of areolae, which are up to 1 mm diam. and with marginal, black, granular soralia. The Norwegian material is sterile. The other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nylander" authorityYear="1853" class="Lichinomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Peltula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Peltula" order="Lichinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Peltula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Nordic countries, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. euploca" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="euploca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">P. euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ach.) Poelt, differs in forming much larger, peltate squamules, up to 5 mm diam. The Norwegian specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wetmore" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Zahlbr." class="Lichinomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Peltula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Peltula placodizans" order="Lichinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="placodizans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Peltula placodizans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identified with some uncertainty, as the material for comparison (17 specimens from Europe, Africa, Australia, and North and South America, borrowed from GZU), was often more olivaceous brown than the dark brown Norwegian material (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Peltula placodizans (O L- 158470). Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.11.6670.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/64933" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">8</figureCitation>
). Wetmore (1970) indicates that the species is probably a complex of several taxa.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973742" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.11.6670.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/64933" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Figure 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wetmore" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Zahlbr." class="Lichinomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Peltula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Peltula placodizans" order="Lichinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="placodizans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Peltula placodizans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(O L-158470). Scale: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
In Norway, the species was found on a vertical wall of calcareous rock in a steep, west-facing hillside. The site has apparently previously been an open or sparsely wooded pasture, but is now in the process of being transformed into spruce forest. Other remarkable lichens collected at the site include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henssen" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Th. Fr." class="Lichinomycetes" family="Lichinaceae" genus="Metamelanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Metamelanea caesiella" order="Lichinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caesiella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Metamelanea caesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Th.Fr.) Henssen, 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Physciaceae" genus="Physcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Physcia dimidiata" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Physcia dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Arnold) Nyl., 
<taxonomicName class="Lichinomycetes" family="Lichinaceae" genus="Thallinocarpon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Thallinocarpon nigritellum" order="Lichinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nigritellum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Thallinocarpon nigritellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lettau) P.M.
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørg">Jorg</normalizedToken>
., and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jatta" authorityYear="1911" baseAuthorityName="Anzi" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Catillariaceae" genus="Toninia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Toninia alutacea" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="alutacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Toninia alutacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Anzi) Jatta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
